					<dt class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-49072">
<span class="avatar"></span>
<span class="comment_num"><a href="#comment-49072" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">1</a></span>
<span class="comment_author">Anony Mouse</span>
<span class="comment_time">December 20, 2011 at 3:01 am</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-49072">
<p>With 7.91 million BTC issued at present and daily issuance occurring at the targeted 7,200 BTC per day, the currency is inflating presently at the annual rate of about 33%.  That is lower than the rate about a year ago &#8212; when the 7,200 per day represented about a 50% pace.  This currency inflation rate will slow with every block (targeted to occur every ten minutes), and a year from now that 7,200 per day will represent about a 25% rate &#8212; on an annual basis.</p>
<p>But then, at the point that 10.5 bitcoins are issued, the daily rate drops by half &#8212; to just 3,600 BTC per day.  And the annual rate of currency inflation at that point takes in instant drop to just 12.5% then (3,600 * 365 / 10,500,000) and continues to slow gradually every block at the 3,600 per day pace for the next four years thereafter.</p>
</div>
					</dd>
					<dt class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-49127">
<span class="avatar"><a href="http://www.runtogold.com" rel="nofollow"></a></span>
